<doc id="216514" wikidata="Q534739" url="?curid=216514" title="Tree and Leaf">
<text>Tree and Leaf is a small anthology of works by J. R. R. Tolkien published in 1964 and originally illustrated by Pauline Baynes which consisted of: 
* a revised version of an essay called &quot;On Fairy-Stories&quot; (originally published in 1947 in &quot;Essays Presented to Charles Williams&quot;)
* an allegorical short story called &quot;Leaf by Niggle&quot; (originally published in the &quot;Dublin Review&quot; in 1945).
Both pieces were re-issued in the collection &quot;The Tolkien Reader&quot; (1966), and have also appeared in various subsequent collections.
Tolkien&#x27;s poem &quot;Mythopoeia&quot; was added to the 1988 second edition (), and his poem &quot;The Homecoming of Beorhtnoth Beorhthelm&#x27;s Son&quot; was added in the 2001 third edition ().

